hors were employed to both separate the end of history from a narrative framework and to map the liminal relation between history and eschatology.Drawing on theories and practices as disparate as constructivism, non-Euclidean geometry, photography, and urban architecture, Shapes of Time presents original connections between modernism, theology, and mathematics as played out within the canon of twentieth-century German letters. Concepts of temporal and spatial form, McGillen contends, contribute to the understanding not only of modernist literature but also of larger theoretical concerns within modern cultural and intellectual history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMathematics in literature. 0aModernism (Literature)zEurope, German-speaking. 0aTime in literature. 4aGerman Studies. 4aPhilosophy. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aJoseph Frank, spatialization, mathematics, Karl Barth, Franz Rosenzweig, Siegfried Kracauer, Robert Musil.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z9783111318264oZDB-23-DSP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501772849?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501772849423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501772849/original  a978-3-11-075183-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131918-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 